Troops of 130 battalion with the support of Army Super Camp, Baga, after a fierce encounter with Boko Haram terrorists and ISWAP criminals have killed 20 of them in Baga town, Borno State. Coordinator, Defence Media Operations, Major General John Enenche, in a statement yesterday, said the operation took place on May 17. He explained that the criminals were heading to attack villages surrounding Baga when the troops attacked their convoy and killed most of them. He said that the criminals were armed with mortars, rocket propelled grenades and small arms hence the troops recovered six AK 47 rifles, 520 rounds of 7.62mm special ammunition and five 36 hand grenades. Enenche said that nine of troops were wounded in action with no loss of life hence they were taking to Sector 3 Hospital for treatment. Dear valued readers, subscribe to the Daily Trust e-paper to continue enjoying our diet of authoritative news. Kindly subscribe here